
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName false

class Provider {
  - name: String
  - location: String
}

class Cruise {
  - cruiseNumber: String
  - name: String
  - startDate: Date
  - endDate: Date
}

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - ssn: String
}

class Guest {
  - name: String
  - isVIP: Boolean
}

class Ship {
  - name: String
  - numberOfDecks: Integer
  - length: Double
  - passengerCapacity: Integer
}

class TravelAgency {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class Booking {
  - bookingNumber: String
  - bookingDate: Date
}

class DestinationArea {
  - name: String
  - seaName: String
}

class Show {
  - title: String
  - duration: Integer
}

class Ticket {
  - ticketId: String
}

' Relationships

Provider "1" --> "0..*" Cruise : organizes
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Employee : requires
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Guest : has
Cruise "1" --> "1" Ship : uses
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Booking : booked through
Booking "1" --> "1" TravelAgency : made by
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" DestinationArea : heads for
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Show : offers
Guest "1" --> "0..*" Ticket : has
Ticket "1" --> "1" Cruise : belongs to
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:
- A `Provider` can organize many `Cruise`s.
- Each `Cruise` requires multiple `Employee`s.
- A `Cruise` includes multiple `Guest`s, and a `Guest` can be in multiple `Cruise`s.
- A `Cruise` uses one `Ship`.
- A `Cruise` is booked via a `Booking`, which is made by a `TravelAgency`.
- A `Cruise` has a destination `DestinationArea`.
- A `Cruise` offers multiple `Show`s.
- A `Guest` can have multiple `Ticket`s (one per cruise), and each `Ticket` belongs to exactly one `Cruise`.

